message:
Hmmm, INTC doesn't support this now, but that's a great idea!

For now, you'd have to work around it by providing your own property, something like:

MemoryStream Media  
{  
 get { return intc.IsCompleted ? intc.Result : new MemoryStream(); }  
}

And then raise the property changed event for that property when the intc.TaskCompleted is done:

private Task RaiseMediaPropertyChangedWhenIntcCompletesAsync()  
{  
 await intc.TaskCompleted;  
 RaisePropertyChanged("Media");  
}
